    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n4100" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐφ - οράω</span></b> , fut. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐπόψομαι, ἐπιόψομαι</span>, aor. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐπεῖδον</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">look upon, behold, watch
            over;</span> (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">Ζεύς</span>) <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀνθρώπους ἐφορᾷ καὶ τί̄νυται ὅς κεν ἁμάρτῃ</span>,
            <i><span class="en">Od. 13.214</span></i>; also ‘go to see’
          (visere), <i><span class="en">Od. 7.324</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 23.19</span></i>, and ‘look up’ (in order to
          choose), here the form <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐπιόψομαι, Ι
            167</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 2.294</span></i>; fig.,
          ‘live to see,’ <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κακά</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 22.61</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
